xepo@csd4.csd.uwm.edu (Scott R Violet) writes:


>	The subject pretty much says it all.  Any know of a good book
>for the beginner in cryptography?  It doesn't have to be to technical,
>but some examples and actual uses would be nice.  Thanks,

A good book is "Cryptography and Data Security" by Dorothy Denning.
It has good sections on cryptography and encryption algorithms, as well as
access controls and information flow security.
